Sequoia Fund, Inc. Key Developments

Sequoia Fund, Inc., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Apr 13, 2017
Mar 24 17
Sequoia Fund, Inc., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Apr 13, 2017, at 16:30 US Eastern Standard Time. Location: Brasserie 8 , 9 West 57th Street New York, NY 10019 United States Agenda: To consider and vote upon the approval of a new investment advisory contract between the corporation and Ruane, Cunniff & Goldfarb Inc.; and to consider any other business that may properly come before the Meeting and any postponement or adjournment thereof.


Sequoia Fund Wins Dismissal of Lawsuit over Huge Valeant Stake
Feb 25 17
A New York state judge has dismissed a lawsuit accusing the Sequoia Fund, known for its ties to Warren Buffett, of recklessly making a huge, disastrous investment in Valeant Pharmaceuticals International Inc, causing billions of dollars of losses. Justice O. Peter Sherwood of the State Supreme Court in White Plains, New York, said Sequoia shareholders failed to show it would have been futile, prior to suing in January 2016, to demand that the mutual fund's directors step in to unwind the investment because of their alleged conflicts of interest. The judge said the shareholders could try to amend their complaint, but that this appeared to be "a fool's errand." Sherwood issued his ruling during a Feb. 15 hearing. A transcript was made public eight days later. Sequoia shareholders had sued Sequoia's Ruane, Cunniff & Goldfarb; portfolio managers Robert Goldfarb and David Poppe; and three directors including author and chairman Roger Lowenstein. The defendants were accused of gross negligence for letting Sequoia plow nearly one-third of its assets into Valeant, despite a policy capping its stake at 25%. Lawyers for the shareholders did not immediately respond to requests for comment on Friday. Valeant shares have tumbled 93% in the last 1-1/2 years amid criticism of the Canadian drug company's pricing and business practices, and regulatory and congressional probes. Goldfarb, who co-managed Sequoia for 36 years, retired as Ruane, Cunniff's chief executive last March. Sequoia sold its last Valeant shares in June, but its losses have left it still trailing 98% of its peers over five years, while assets have shrunk by more than half to USD 4.2 billion.


Sequoia Fund, Inc., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Sep 12, 2016
Aug 18 16
Sequoia Fund, Inc., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Sep 12, 2016, at 09:00 US Eastern Standard Time. Location: Brasserie 8, 9 West 57th Street New York, NY, 10019 United States Agenda: To consider and vote upon the election of three directors of the corporation, each such director to serve a term of indefinite duration and until his successor is duly elected and qualifies; and to consider any other matters.


