About 
                                Sequoia Fund







 











 About Us
                    Sequoia Fund is a mutual fund advised by Ruane, Cunniff & Goldfarb Inc since its founding in 1969. In managing the Fund, Ruane, Cunniff pursues a value-oriented approach, seeking to outperform over the long-term by purchasing shares, at prices below our estimated range of their intrinsic values, in high-quality businesses that have significant and durable competitive advantages and that we believe can compound the Fund's capital at attractive rates over the long-term.

We invest with the mindset of a business owner, because we believe that the only reliable way to value stocks and invest in them successfully is to think of them as interests in the long-term profits of a business.

The long-term perspective we take informs how we think, what we do, and how we construct our portfolios. We focus exclusively on things we can understand, like the quality of a business franchise, the competence of a management team, and the structure of an industry, rather than factors we consider inherently unpredictable, like the direction of the economy or the sentiment of the stock market.

We spend virtually all of our time researching the strengths, weaknesses and prospects of individual companies. Because this work is painstaking and difficult, we focus our holdings on a small group of businesses. This focus allows us to know what we own, and should also allow us to outperform if we use our research to make thoughtful judgments.





