Leader of Valeant Investor Sequoia Resigns
Robert Goldfarb step downs; fund hit hard by its heavy exposure to Valeant

 






By

Sarah Krouse and 
              

Sarah Krouse
The Wall Street Journal
BiographySarah Krouse
@bysarahkrouse
sarah.krouse@wsj.com



Daisy Maxey


Daisy Maxey
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyDaisy Maxey
@DaisyMaxey
daisy.maxey.7
Google+
daisy.maxey@wsj.com




  Updated March 23, 2016 10:09 p.m. ET





The woes of Valeant Pharmaceuticals International Inc. claimed another casualty Wednesday as investing legend Robert Goldfarb stepped down from a mutual fund with a big stake in the drugmaker. The 71-year-old Mr. Goldfarb was the longtime leader of Sequoia Fund Inc., a well-known investment product with historical ties to Warren Buffett. The fund had lost 10.9% through Tuesday and has underperformed 98% of its peers so far this year,...
  


